...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 6 PM
EDT THIS EVENING...
...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM TO 6 PM EDT
SATURDAY...

* WHAT...For the first Small Craft Advisory, south winds 5 to 10 
  kt with gusts up to 20 kt expected. For the second Small Craft 
  Advisory, west winds 10 to 15 kt with gusts up to 25 kt 
  expected.

* WHERE...Tidal Potomac River from Key Bridge to Smith Point VA, 
  and Chesapeake Bay and adjoining estuaries north of Smith 
  Point VA.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, from noon today to 6 PM 
  EDT this evening. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 9 AM to 6 
  PM EDT Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.

PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...

Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

